&quot;Robert Low Bacon (July 23, 1884 – September 12, 1938) was an American politician, a banker, Lieutenant Colonel, and congressman from New York.&quot;
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_L._Bacon" rel="nofollow">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_L._Bacon</a>

The photo was taken on board of the steamship New York, see <a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83030193/1915-12-28/ed-1/seq-3/" rel="nofollow">The evening world., December 28, 1915, Final Edition, Image 3</a>, column 7 &quot;Had Rough Time on the Atlantic, But Smallest Dog Survived It - ... Robert Bacon was also on the New York. He decried any talk of dlssensions between the allies. He brings back a report on the American Ambulance Corps In France that he went abroad to compile. He says the corps is doing splendid work and should not be Interrupted for lack of funds.&quot;
